						               													<description>The British Navy at bay - part two&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Clash of Arms Games continues to explore warfare in the age of the fighting sail with Monsoon Seas. Monsoon Seas is Volume III of Mark Campbell's naval warfare Close Action series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This set of special rules and scenarios covers mainly the 1777-1783 campaigns of French Admiral Pierre-Andre de Suffren and his battles with the Royal Navy in the South Atlantic and Indian Ocean (seventeen scenarios). The first three scenarios concern the Spanish-Portuguese War of 1776-1777 over what would become Uruguay.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;20+ Scenarios explore the dramatic engagements and set piece battles of: Sadras, Providien, Negapatam, Trincomalee, Cuddalore and more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This set of specific rules (72 pages), scenarios and historical commentary is a worthy successor to her highly acclaimed sister games Close Action: The Age of Fighting Sail Vol. 1 and Rebel Seas: The British Navy at Bay Part I.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(source: Clash fo Arms website and user's description))&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
